model_patch.ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompres:
Looking at the code:
```cpp
for (int i = 0; i < bits; i++) {
    int j = dis(generate);
    tmp += (i < offset) ? ('0' + j) : ('a' + j - offset);
}
```

The linter warning indicates that `i < offset` is always true because `offset >= bits` (the loop runs from 0 to bits-1). This means the else branch (`'a' + j - offset`) is never executed.

The fix is to simplify the code by removing the unreachable branch:

```diff
--- a/ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompress/uncompress.cpp
+++ b/ohos_7zip/library/src/main/cpp/uncompress/uncompress.cpp
@@ -43,7 +43,7 @@ std::string Uncompress::generateFileName() {
     for (int i = 0; i < bits; i++) {
         int j = dis(generate);
-        tmp += (i < offset) ? ('0' + j) : ('a' + j - offset);
+        tmp += '0' + j;
     }
     tmp += ".ohos";
     return tmp;
```

